bill.summary:
9/17/2008--Passed House without amendment. (This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary has been expanded because action occurred on the measure.)
Congratulates the men and women of the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) on the occasion of its 100th Anniversary;
Honors the heroic sacrifice of the FBI employees who have given their lives, or have been wounded or injured, in the service of the United States. Thanks all the men and women of the FBI for their efforts to protect and defend the American people from domestic and foreign threats and for their dedication to the pursuit of justice through the rule of law.
